            <p:rationale>This service is specifically designed for managing business rules and ensures that these rules are easier to adjust than if they are hard coded. Such a service requires less technical expertise, making the business rules an asset that analysts can maintain themselves. By managing business rules separately, they can be reused more easily.</p:rationale>
            <p:implications>Business rules are explicitly identified and documented in the analysis phase. The complexity and immutability of each business line is determined. Each distinct business rule type (acceptance rule, process control, etc.) is the correct business rule that management sought to manage this effect. The operation can adapt the business rules, even while other parts of the application are developing and changing with business demands.</p:implications>
